New Records: The Los Angeles Dodgers clinched their 11th National League West division title in the last 12 years, and their 23rd division crown overall.
Key Match Events: Will Smith hit the game-tying home run.
Shohei Ohtani singled in the go-ahead run.
Mookie Betts delivered a two-run single.
Andy Pages hit a two-run home run for extra insurance runs.
Walker Buehler pitched brilliantly, allowing just one run with five hits in five innings.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Dave Roberts expressed pride in his team, stating, 'I couldn't be more proud of these guys. They fought and fought and fought and overcame adversity.'
Shohei Ohtani expressed happiness about clinching the division title, saying, 'I'm really happy. Today I came to the stadium really wanting to clinch.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: First baseman Freddie Freeman left the game with a right ankle injury.
The Dodgers will look to secure the best record in the NL and the number one overall seed as they head to Colorado for the final series of the regular season.
